column9: The risk or severity of adverse effects can be increased when Loxoprofen is combined with Morniflumate.
The risk or severity of adverse effects can be increased when Aceclofenac is combined with Talniflumate.
Cefroxadine may decrease the excretion rate of Pyrazinamide which could result in a higher serum level.
Valaciclovir may decrease the excretion rate of Oseltamivir which could result in a higher serum level.
The risk or severity of adverse effects can be increased when Loxoprofen is combined with Talniflumate.
Lysergic acid diethylamide may increase the vasoconstricting activities of Lisuride.
Nalmefene may decrease the excretion rate of Naldemedine which could result in a higher serum level.
The risk or severity of adverse effects can be increased when Dexketoprofen is combined with NS-398.
The risk or severity of adverse effects can be increased when Trospium is combined with Biperiden.
